The paper deals with Embodied Question Answering, which involves an agent interacting with an environment to gather information for answering user questions. This falls under the domain of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses navigation, which involves the agent moving through the environment, and this could be related to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions a distillation network, which is a technique used in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL).
